Global Protein Supplements Market Insights
Protein Supplements Market size was valued at USD 25.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 44.8 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 7.6% from 2024 to 2030.

Protein Supplements Market Overview
The global protein supplements market is valued at approximately USD 24.4 billion in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 45.5 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 9.3% during the forecast period. This growth is driven by the increasing health consciousness among consumers, a rise in fitness and bodybuilding culture, and a shift toward plant-based protein sources. Protein supplements are used to improve muscle mass, aid in weight loss, and enhance recovery post-exercise. With a growing number of fitness enthusiasts and health-conscious individuals, the demand for protein supplements is expected to continue rising globally.

